lenders.name: Roberta
lenders.occupational_info:
Roberta Chadis is a business owner, author, speaker and co-host of a local cable TV show.  As founder of Dog Health News™ she has brought dog health and wellness to a new height focusing on educating others through training videos, newscasts, news bulletins and breaking news to make your dog well with innovative strategies to lower your costs for dog health care. Chadis has devoted her life to providing information and trainings that support dog health and wellness to make the quality of life for dogs better throughout the world.  Her ability to inspire dog parents to challenge their behavior and be honest about how they care for their dog has made Dog Health News™ a regular source of reliable strategies and resources for dog lovers and dog health professionals.

Roberta’s vision to make a difference in the health of dogs worldwide is the driving force for dogged determination to build a network of people who want to improve their dog’s lives and not overspend on unnecessary dog medications and dog healthcare services.
 
Author of “Good Boy Jesse”,  a story that is narrated by her Golden Retriever, Roberta describes her dog’s life with Mom and Dad.  Good Boy Jesse is available in English, Italian and Spanish accompanied by an audio CD & DVD.  Roberta serves on many boards including and was recently honored to be included in the “Legendary Locals of Salem Massachusetts” published in 2013.
